				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\eta =\frac{{\int }_{{t}_{1}}^{{t}_{2}}{p}_{avg}dt}{{\int }_{{t}_{1}}^{{t}_{2}}{p}_{max}dt}$$\end{document}

The algorithm begins tracking at moment t1 and ends at time t2. The average power produced between t1 and t2 is denoted by pavg\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${p}_{avg}$$\end{document}, and the theoretical maximum power available is denoted by pmax\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
