In spite of advances in PV technology, partial shading has a negative impact on the system and results in power loss. Shading loss is the term used to describe the power loss caused by shading, which is defined as the difference in power between total maximum power obtained under PSC (pmpp,shading) and under STC (pmpp,without shading) [30], as:42pmpp,shadingloss=pmpp,withoutshading-pmpp,shading\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
